import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='u', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean = {data['u'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median = {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'u'?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='diff', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['diff'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['diff'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(x=data['diff'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['diff'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'diff'?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('diff')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
